text.tspan: Do more people live in urban or rural areas? 2025
“Majority urban” means that over 50% of the population resides in urban areas, whereas “majority rural”
means that 50% or more resides in rural areas.
Data source: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2018); HYDE (2023)
Note: Because the estimates of city and metropolitan areas are based on national definitions of what constitutes a city or metropolitan area,
cross-country comparisons should be made with caution.
